{"title_page": "Reinhard P\u00f6llath", "text_new": "'''Reinhard P\u00f6llath''' (born January 15, 1948) is a [[Germany|German]] businessman and lawyer.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.munzinger.de/search/portrait/Reinhard+P%C3%B6llath/0/24305.html|title=Reinhard P\u00f6llath - Munzinger Biographie|last=Ravensburg|first=Munzinger-Archiv GmbH|website=www.munzinger.de|language=de|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref> He serves as Chairman of the Board of Directors of [[Beiersdorf]].<ref>[http://www.beiersdorf.com/about_us/boards_committees/supervisory_board_committees.html Beiersdorf Boards & Committees]</ref><ref name=\"business\">[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=8376887&ticker=SZZ:GR&previousCapId=876083&previousTitle=Beiersdorf%20AG BusinessWeek]</ref><ref>[http://quotes.wsj.com/XE/BEI/company-people The Wall Street Journal]</ref>\n\n==Early live and education==\nReinhard P\u00f6llath was born in 1948. He grew up in [[Upper Franconia]], where his family has run a [[Woodworking joints|joinery]] since the 17th century.<ref name=\":0\" /> He graduated from high school in [[Marktredwitz]] in 1967.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.frankenpost.de/dossiers/art3071,633482|title=Geldverdienen kann nicht alles sein|last=|first=|date=|work=Frankenpost|access-date=2018-09-15|language=de-DE}}</ref> After completing his military service, he studied law from 1969 to 1973  at the [[University of Regensburg]] and the [[Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich]]. Subsequently, he held a scholarship from the [[Studienstiftung]], with whose support he graduated with a master's degree from the [[Harvard Law School]] in 1974. In 2006, he obtained a doctorate degree.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1977, he was admitted as a lawyer and worked first as a lawyer in [[Munich]], [[Frankfurt|Frankfurt am Main]] and [[Berlin]]. Until 1993, he was a partner at a law firm in Munich and until 1997, managing director of a real estate and hotel company.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.frankenpost.de/region/marktredwitz/Professor-Poellath-stiftet-Jean-Paul-Bueste;art2442,2477942|title=Professor P\u00f6llath stiftet Jean-Paul-B\u00fcste|last=|first=|date=|work=Frankenpost|access-date=2018-09-15|language=de-DE}}</ref>\n\nIn 1997, together with six partners, he started the [[law firm]] P+P P\u00f6llath + Partners.<ref name=\"business\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pplaw.com/de/artikel/aktuelles/einfachgutgemacht-20-jahre-pp-poellath-partners|title=20 Jahre P+P P\u00f6llath + Partners|website=P+P P\u00f6llath + Partners|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> He specialized in advising family businesses, corporate acquisitions, tax law, foundations and trusts. P\u00f6llath has advised different recognized clients, like the [[Harald Quandt family]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mpg.de/foerdererportrait-poellath|title=F\u00f6rderer-Portrait|website=Max-Planck-Gesellschaft|language=de|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> In 2012, the law firm had offices in Munich, Berlin and Frankfurt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tool.handelsblatt.com/tabelle/index.php?id=101&so=2a&pc=25&po=1050|title=Handelsblatt Legal Success: Das sind Deutschlands beste Wirtschaftsanw\u00e4lte - Handelsblatt Online|website=tool.handelsblatt.com|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> P\u00f6llath became known as an advisor to the Herz family, which appointed him interim chief executive officer of [[Tchibo]] Holding AG, in 2002.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/archiv/der-neue-vorstandschef-der-tchibo-holding-ag-reinhard-poellath-der-besonnene-schlichter/2193502.html|title=Der Neue Vorstandschef der Tchibo-Holding AG: Reinhard P\u00f6llath: Der besonnene Schlichter|access-date=2018-09-16|language=de}}</ref> One year later, he was nominated as chairman of the supervisory board.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/artikel/a-261786.html|title=Tchibo: Familie Herz geht getrennte Wege - manager magazin|work=manager magazin|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> In 2007, he took over management of Brost Holding, which held 50 percent of the [[Funke Mediengruppe]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.manager-magazin.de/digitales/it/a-470765.html|title=WAZ-Gruppe: Brost-Holding mit neuer F\u00fchrung - manager magazin|work=manager magazin|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>\n\n== Other affiliations ==\nP\u00f6llath is an Honorary Professor at the [[University of M\u00fcnster|University of M\u00fcnster's]] Institute of tax law.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pplaw.com/de/berater/poellath-reinhard|title=Prof. Dr. Reinhard P\u00f6llath, LL.M.|website=P+P P\u00f6llath + Partners|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>\n\nHe sits on the Boards of [[SinnerSchrader]], [[Woolworth GmbH]], [[BonVenture]], [[TA Triumph-Adler]], and Beiersdorf.<ref name=\"business\" />  He was chairman of the board of [[Escada]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/wirtschaft/modekonzern-neustart-fuer-escada/1260620.html|title=Neustart f\u00fcr Escada|date=2008-06-20|work=Der Tagesspiegel Online|access-date=2018-09-16|language=de-DE|issn=1865-2263}}</ref>\n\nP\u00f6llath is a member of the council for the [[Lindau Nobel Laureate Meetings]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lindau-nobel.org/about/|title=About|work=The Lindau Nobel Laureate Meetings|access-date=2018-09-17|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Engelhorn tax affair ==\nIn 2013, P\u00f6llath was put into investigative custody for nine days, following suspicions of aiding in the evasion of gift taxes in the amount of up to 440 million Euro by the pharmaceutical billionaire [[Curt Engelhorn]], whose assets P\u00f6llath managed. The tax rebate negotiated with the authorities by the Engelhorn family is said to amount to around 135 million Euro.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/soziales/engelhorn-clan-kann-auf-steuer-deal-hoffen-a-1073408.html|title=Curt Engelhorn: Milliard\u00e4rs-Clan kann auf Steuer-Deal hoffen|date=2016-01-23|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/bayern/Haben-zwei-Millionaers-Toechter-80-Millionen-Euro-hinterzogen-id36690557.html|title=Haben zwei Million\u00e4rs-T\u00f6chter 80 Millionen Euro hinterzogen?|last=Richter|first=Peter|work=Augsburger Allgemeine|access-date=2018-09-16|language=de}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nThe asteroid [[List of minor planets: 7001\u20138000|7448 P\u00f6llath]], which was discovered on the day before his birth, was named after him. P\u00f6llath was awarded the [[Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]], first class.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-141826665.html|title=Steuern: Zwischen Erde und Mond|last=Neumann|first=Conny|date=2016-01-23|work=Der Spiegel|access-date=2018-09-17|last2=Richter|first2=Peter|volume=4}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pollath, Reinhard}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:University of Regensburg alumni]]\n[[Category:Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich alumni]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of M\u00fcnster faculty]]\n[[Category:German businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Officers Crosses of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]]\n[[Category:Beiersdorf people]]\n", "text_old": "'''Reinhard P\u00f6llath''' (born January 15, 1948) is a [[Germany|German]] businessman and lawyer.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.munzinger.de/search/portrait/Reinhard+P%C3%B6llath/0/24305.html|title=Reinhard P\u00f6llath - Munzinger Biographie|last=Ravensburg|first=Munzinger-Archiv GmbH|website=www.munzinger.de|language=de|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref> He serves as Chairman of the Board of Directors of [[Beiersdorf]].<ref>[http://www.beiersdorf.com/about_us/boards_committees/supervisory_board_committees.html Beiersdorf Boards & Committees]</ref><ref name=\"business\">[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?pers